This paper is about a neural network-based system for Word Sense Disambiguation (WSD) for German, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also uses semantic embeddings and optimization methods, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses lexical resources and networks, which are relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
